<doc id="113355" wikidata="Q3253482" url="?curid=113355" title="List of English Heritage properties">
<text>English Heritage is a registered charity that manages the National Heritage Collection. This comprises over 400 of England&#x27;s historic buildings, monuments, and sites spanning more than 5,000 years of history. It has direct ownership over some historic sites and also liaises with private owners of sites that are managed under guardianship arrangements.

The following is a list of English Heritage properties containing links for any stately home, historic house, castle, abbey, museum or other property in the care of English Heritage.

